dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

srcinfo.srccontr: Source data is MassGIS Level II-compliant digital parcel file, in ESRI personal geodatabase format. This geodatabase was originally automated using ESRI ArcGIS in 2005 from 31 assessor's maps at 1" = 100'.

procstep.procdesc: This town's CAMA data was linked to several hundred individual condo footprint polygons. To conform to the MassGIS model, these condos were placed in the M110Misc feature class, and assessor records aggregated to link to master parcels.
Existing Level II parcel data was converted to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase and additional data layers and tables were added.
Spatial accuracy of data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines; town boundary was verified to be coincident with MassGIS Town Boundary layer. Polygon topology was updated and validated.

Multi-part polygons were created where necessary; internal polygon boundaries were dissolved where necessary; polygons representing legal boundaries such as easements or private right-of-ways were created. LOC_ID was updated

Updates were made to the Level II data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of spring 2011, for the town's FY 2012. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

Updates were made to the Level III data for FY2018 and FY2019. CAMA data for FY2018 was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

Updates were made to the Level III data for FY2019 and FY2020. CAMA data for FY2018 was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

overview.dsoverv: Tax parcel polygons for Blackstone, MA. This data set contains polygons which delineate property ownership in the town of Blackstone, according to the assessor's tax maps as of September 2019. It is formatted in compliance with the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files, Version 2.0. This data set is considered to be MassGIS Level III-compliant and is derived from an upgrade of the previous Level II-compliant version of this same data set.

distinfo.resdesc: M032TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Blackstone, MA that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M032Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M032OthLeg and M032Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

M032TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Blackstone, MA that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M032Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M032OthLeg and M032Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
